Philippine Stocks: Atlas Mining, Cebu Air, Philex, SM Prime

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-20T04:19:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/philippine-stocks-cebu-air-philex-mining-sm-prime-holdings.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.7 percent to
4,274.77, completing a 0.5 percent gain this week. The stock
market will be shut on April 21 and 22 for holidays.  Atlas Consolidated Mining & Development (AT)  Corp, the
nation’s fourth-largest metals producer by market value,
advanced 1.8 percent to 15.96 pesos, the steepest advance since
April 4. Carmen Copper Corp., a subsidiary of Atlas, forecasts
sales of $349 million this year, a stock exchange filing showed.  Cebu Air Inc. (CEB)  , the largest budget carrier, climbed
2.9 percent to 79.95 pesos, the steepest advance since March 1.
The airline said the number of passengers increased 12 percent
in the first quarter to 2.8 million, putting it on course to
meet the target of 12 million this year. The first-quarter
growth was driven by international traffic, which rose 32
percent, it said.    Manila Mining Corp. (MAB) ’s Class A shares (MA PM), which are
reserved for Filipinos, climbed 8.6 percent to 3.8 centavos, the
highest since November 1995 after Chairman Felipe Yap said talks
with  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)   for a venture on the Kalayaan
project are “progressing well” and an agreement may be
concluded “soon.” Manila Mining Class B shares (MAB PM), which
have no ownership restrictions, gained 2.7 percent to 3.8
centavos, the highest since May 2007. Philex advanced 4 percent
to 17.74 pesos, bound for the highest since Dec. 3, 2009.  SM Prime Holdings Inc. (SMPH)  , the largest mall
developer, increased 1.9 percent to 11.92 pesos, the highest
since April 11. The company said first-quarter profit rose 12
percent to 2.12 billion pesos ($49 million) from a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
